	     Dakar - Marriage before the age of 18 is common in rural Senegal, nearly one of three girls gets married as a child. The World Bank and Save the Children say that nearly 20 000 underage girls marry every day around the world. Al Jazeera met with Ndey, a west African child bride who shared her story. Watch as she speak here.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  